All-inclusive model auditions FDCIx Lakmé Fashion Week gives you the opportunity to walk the runway by being part of its online auditions.

How to apply:

Step 1: Upload a video of your best walk on Instagram. Make sure to tag FDCI & Lakmé Fashion Week handles and add #FDCIXLFWModelAuditions to your reel.

(High resolution full length walk video: Duration 20 to 30
seconds)

Step 2: Fill in the Registration form with the link in bio

Criteria for application : Valid work visa for International Models

Final selections to take place via online polling

JJ Valaya presented his collection titled 'Alma' at FDCI #ICW2022

The collection marked the celebration of 30 years of the label and takes inspiration from Spain.
Luxurious fabrics, elegant details, inspired prints and the designer’s timeless and much loved embroideries define this season’s Couture collection in all its glory as it transcends its journey blending the designer’s ethos with that of Spain.

@lotus_herbals @htcityshowstoppers @archanaaggarwalofficial @tencel_luxe @officialjiotv 

#ICW2022 #15YearsofICW #FDCI

#ICW2022 | Here’s a glimpse at Couturier @rahulmishra_7 show at the FDCI India Couture Week 2022. 

Rahul Mishra presented his collection titled 'The Tree of Life'. It emerges from deep emotion and nostalgia.

Two and three dimensional embroideries articulate the first flush of nature emerging on the surface of a body, and life that grows from it. Intricately embellished surfaces articulate scenes from dense forests with ancient architectural remains and vegetation in modern day silhouettes. A fresh application for the brand, metallics add another dimension to the brand’s signature hand craft.

The collection saw playful multicoloured lehengas to long jackets over lehengas and red sindoori sarees to well-tailored men’s wear with the traditional magic of drapes. The seamless magic of the finest embroidery techniques such as the jarkana, pichwai, kashida formed the strong craft pillars for this collection.

#FDCIManifestWeddingWeekend #FMWW2025 #FDCI #Manifest

#FMWW2025: "We wanted to create something for a very exclusive kind of customer who only wanted to come in,” says Mr. Sunil Sethi, Chairman, FDCI.

What began as an idea has grown into a landmark moment on the wedding calendar—The FDCI Manifest Wedding Weekend: a space where craftsmanship, couture, and emotion come together for those who dream beyond the ordinary.

At the heart of it all is Mr. Sethi—a visionary who saw weddings not just as ceremonies, but as deeply personal stories waiting to be told through couture, culture, and craft. In this conversation, he reflects on the larger vision—and how this intimate yet iconic celebration came to life.

Tune in!

Editorial Direction: Meghna Sharma (@sharmameghna )
Digital Editor: Salva Mubarak (@herbertspoultry )
Social Media Manager: Vishvi Gupta (@vishviiii )

@fdciofficial @rpsg.lifestylemedia @sunilsethifdci @avarna_jain
